node.text:
Racing down LA’s Melrose Avenue in the California sun, supermodel #AlessandraAmbrosio takes on Vogue’s latest Shopping Challenge. The goal? She must style three animal-print outfits for three occasions, in just 60 minutes. Watch as she embraces her wild side as she styles a selection of looks for a brunch, job interview and party. 

This episode of The Shopping Challenge was filmed pre-pandemic and before social distancing guidelines were issued.

node.text: “I definitely feel like young girls are being made to grow up far quicker than they are and not celebrating the actual age they are at,” CEO of @BlackGirlFest, @NKrystal_, tells #BritishVogue in the second instalment of @TheOfficialPandora’s speaker series: ‘10 Minutes With’. Watch as the young entrepreneur talks through her inspirations, mentors and how embracing your own uniqueness can be used to your advantage.

node.text: It’s a well-known fact that wearing SPF is one of the best ways to protect your skin – but how do you do it right to avoid signs of ageing and pigmentation? Watch as #BritishVogue’s beauty and lifestyle director @JessicaDiner does a sunscreen deep dive with @LaRochePosay dermatologist Dr Hiva Fassihi to discuss how to incorporate SPF into your everyday make-up routine (and why make-up with SPF isn’t enough), the difference between the effects of ultraviolet A and ultraviolet B on your skin, and why it’s important to apply sunscreen even if you’re not leaving the house.

node.title: Face Facts: The Importance Of SPF No Matter The Season

node.text: It’s not a bag. It’s a Baguette. Die-hard #SexAndTheCity fans will know the significance of #CarrieBradshaw’s cult @Fendi accessory – the archetypal It bag was the first major designer piece to appear in the character’s now legendary wardrobe. And though early glimpses from the set of #AndJustLikeThat suggest the columnist’s look has evolved now she’s in her fifties, rest assured she’s refusing to be parted from this particular fashion classic. Click the link in bio for more on the Baguette’s cameo in the SATC reboot.

node.text: Last week was full of epic red-carpet moments at Cannes, but the crew-neck jumper #JasonSudeikis wore for the season two premiere of #TedLasso in LA put them all in the shade. Why? The simple slogan on the front: Jadon & Marcus & Bukayo. A gesture of support for the three gifted Black footballers subjected to racial abuse online in the wake of England’s heartbreaking Euro 2020 defeat at Wembley a week ago, Sudeikis had the top printed up himself before the event. At the link in bio, he discusses how the young players “led by example” during the tournament – and why more must be done to kick racism out of sport for good.

node.text:
Serving up one of the best beauty looks from the past week, #GemmaChan complemented her shimmering Oscar de la Renta gown for the #Cannes closing ceremony with rhinestone details under the eyes – the work of British Vogue contributing beauty editor @TheValGarland. Click the link in bio for more of the best beauty looks on the Cannes red carpet – from #AndieMacDowell’s silver hair and red lip combo to #TimotheeChalamet’s Glossier highlighter.

Photographed by Felix Lahrer.

node.text:
“We know each other’s past heartbreaks and failures. We cannot craft an image of ourselves, a light in which to be seen by the other... At times, it feels as though our former friendship is putting too much pressure on our current relationship. But we are living in a world of truth. That foundation – the friendship – means that in the hardest times, we have some history to draw on.” As new research finds two-thirds of couples start out platonically, one writer recounts the decades-long friendship that eventually led to love.

#RichardMadden and #LaraStone photographed by @AlasdairMclellan and styled by @KPhelan123, with hair and grooming by @AnthonyTurnerHair, make-up by @LynseyAlexander and nails by @PebblesNails for the May 2019 issue of #BritishVogue.

node.text: The couture runways are always a testament to the magic of high fashion, and nothing can compare to the romanticism of the wedding gowns. Brides can take comfort in the knowledge that the world’s greatest designers are championing a bold new era in matrimonial dress. Click the link in bio for your rundown of the best wedding looks to grace the AW21 couture runways.

An actor, activist, producer, restaurateur and beauty brand founder, @PriyankaChopra needs little introduction. As she celebrates her birthday today, she speaks to #BritishVogue about beauty regrets, bushy brows and the icon she’d be for a night, at the link in bio.

node.text: When it comes to mapping out your summer wardrobe, look to the warm-weather style of the stars. This summer, “less is more” has been a common theme. #Rihanna and #DuaLipa have turned to midriff flossing and this season’s trendy “curtain reveal”, while #Lizzo has been serving high-octane glamour and #Beyonce has perfected the art of the glamorous finishing touch. Click the link in bio to see how the A-listers are styling their head-turning looks.

node.text: ”Calories weren’t part of the food discussion in the same way money wasn’t really part of the life discussion,” says Emmy-winning #SexAndTheCity writer Cindy Chupack. “SATC was a celebration of those things women often neglect to celebrate, because they’re too busy worrying about their shape, their savings or seeing singledom as a stage to get through before getting married.” As the hype for the reboot ‘And Just Like That’ heightens, click the link in bio to find out why one of the best things about the beloved series is the food.

node.text:
Summer dressing can sometimes feel like an impossible task – especially when the British weather isn’t playing ball. But now is an ideal time to take a long hard look at your clothes and create the perfect summer capsule wardrobe. Just remember the three “re” affixes – rehome, repurpose and rekindle. From the no-fuss throw-on dress to a breezy short-sleeved shirt, click the link in bio for nine styling tricks to employ now.

#GigiHadid photographed by @ZoeGhertner and styled by @SarrJamois, with hair by @TamaraMcNaughton, make-up by @FaraHomidi and set design by @SpencerVrooman for the March 2020 issue of #BritishVogue.

node.text:
Given the option, most of us would rather be sat next to a turquoise swimming pool in some far-flung holiday destination – but even if that dream won’t be a reality for another year, a little bit of escapism never goes amiss. The world’s most stylish women have long had the formula for a great poolside outfit sussed. From #Rihanna to #NaomiCampbell, allow these 31 summer style mavens to show you how poolside perfection is done – and take note for your next getaway.
